# Supabase Auth SSR

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Checks | Does not |
|-------|--------|----------|
| Middleware | Session exists for protected routes | Role / profile (keep middleware light) |
| Layout / page (`requireAdmin`, etc.) | Role and profile | Session refresh (middleware handles cookies) |

## Middleware rules

- Matcher: only routes that need session checks (`/dashboard/:path*`, `/login`) — not every page.
- Use `lib/supabase/middleware.ts` for client creation and cookie helpers.
- **Always** copy refreshed cookies onto redirect responses via `redirectWithCookies()` — never return bare `NextResponse.redirect()` after `getUser()`.
- Do **not** redirect authenticated users from `/login` to `/dashboard` in middleware — login page handles admin-only redirect.

## Permission denial

- Missing session → `/login`
- Authenticated but not permitted → `/access-denied` (never `/login` while session cookie remains — causes redirect loops)

## Server Actions

- After `signInWithPassword`, verify role/profile before `redirect()`.
- On access denied at sign-in, `signOut()` and return form error — do not redirect to a protected route.

## OAuth (when added)

- Add `app/auth/callback/route.ts` with `exchangeCodeForSession`.
- Never run code exchange in middleware.

## Realtime (client)

- No `router.refresh()` inside `onAuthStateChange` without deduping.
- Unsubscribe channels in `useEffect` cleanup.

## Anti-patterns

```ts
// Permission denial sends authenticated user to login
if (!profile || profile.role !== 'admin') redirect('/login')

// Redirect drops refreshed session cookies
return NextResponse.redirect(loginUrl)

// Middleware auto-redirects any session away from login
if (pathname === '/login' && user) redirect('/dashboard')
```
